{"meta": {"centerNodeId": "taxonomy-species-chrysococcyx-klaas", "centerNodeType": "taxonomy", "generatedAt": "2026-05-28T16:28:22", "includedNodeCount": 3, "includedLinkCount": 2, "layoutMode": "precomputed-static"}, "center": {"id": "taxonomy-species-chrysococcyx-klaas", "name": "白腹金鹃", "type": "taxonomy"}, "nodes": [{"id": "taxonomy-species-chrysococcyx-klaas", "name": "白腹金鹃", "latinName": "Chrysococcyx klaas", "type": "taxonomy", "taxonomyLevel": "species", "summary": "白腹金鹃（Chrysococcyx klaas）是图谱中的分类级分类节点，当前关联1种鸟类，如Klaas's cuckoo。", "expandable": true, "memberCount": 1, "x": -911.25, "y": -194.44, "z": 116.66}, {"id": "bird-klaas-s-cuckoo-3d3184c6", "name": "Klaas's cuckoo", "englishName": "Klaas's cuckoo", "latinName": "Chrysococcyx klaas", "type": "bird", "status": "LC", "summary": "Klaas's cuckoo (Chrysococcyx klaas) is a species of cuckoo in the family Cuculidae which is native to the wooded regions of sub-Saharan Africa. The specific name honours Klaas, the Khoikhoi man who collected the type specimen. Name The species was named Le Coucou de Klaas by French explorer François Le Vaillant in 1806, in his book Histoire naturelle des oiseaux d'Afrique in recognition of his Khoikhoi servant and assistant, named Klaas, who found the type specimen. Le Vaillant wrote: ...mon ami Klaas ... Recois l'hommage que je t'adresse ici ... Puissent les naturalistes conserver à l'espèce que je vais décrire, le nom que je lui donne, et consacre ainsi les services que tu m'as rendus: ils me prouveront par là que mes travaux ont eu quelque prix à leurs yeux. Le Vaillant's wish was honoured when the bird's first binomial name, Cuculus klaas, was applied by James Francis Stephens in 1815, and the tribute to Klaas has persisted to the present binomial. The bird is the first known case of a species being named after an Indigenous individual, and Le Vaillant is one of the only colonial biologists to name bird species after local people. Edgar Leopold Layard named the brown-breasted flycatcher after Muttu, his servant. Range The species occurs throughout sub-Saharan Africa with the exception of very arid areas in the south-west. Description Klaas's cuckoo is 16–18 cm (6.3–7.1 inches) in length. The species exhibits sexual dimorphism. Males have a glossy green body with few markings and plain white underparts. Females have a bronze-brown body, greenish wing coverts and faintly barred white underparts. Viewed in flight, the male is largely white with dark primaries and females appear mostly brown. Males and females both have a small white post-ocular patch. Notes References", "shortSummary": "Klaas's cuckoo (Chrysococcyx klaas) is a species of cuckoo in the family Cuculidae which is native to the wooded regions of sub-Saharan Afr…", "locations": ["姆普马兰加省", "James Francis Stephens", "撒哈拉以南非洲"], "lat": -26.0, "lng": 30.0, "imageUrl": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/b/be/Cuckoo_Klaas%27s_2010_10_05_13_53_57.jpg", "order": "Cuculiformes", "family": "Cuculidae", "genus": "Chrysococcyx", "species": "Chrysococcyx klaas", "orderCn": "鹃形目", "familyCn": "杜鹃科", "genusCn": "金鹃属", "speciesCn": "白腹金鹃", "kingdomId": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylumId": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "classId": "taxonomy-class-aves", "orderId": "taxonomy-order-cuculiformes", "familyId": "taxonomy-family-cuculidae", "genusId": "taxonomy-genus-chrysococcyx", "speciesId": "taxonomy-species-chrysococcyx-klaas", "taxonomyIds": {"kingdom": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylum": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "class": "taxonomy-class-aves", "order": "taxonomy-order-cuculiformes", "family": "taxonomy-family-cuculidae", "genus": "taxonomy-genus-chrysococcyx", "species": "taxonomy-species-chrysococcyx-klaas"}, "expandable": true, "x": -911.25, "y": -194.44, "z": 100.56}, {"id": "taxonomy-genus-chrysococcyx", "name": "金鹃属", "latinName": "Chrysococcyx", "type": "taxonomy", "taxonomyLevel": "genus", "summary": "金鹃属（Chrysococcyx）是图谱中的分类级分类节点，当前关联12种鸟类，如翠金鹃、Diederik cuckoo、Klaas's